trans-unit.source: Implements a hash table with the key and the value strongly typed to be strings rather than objects.

trans-unit.source: A key cannot be `null`, but a value can.
trans-unit.target: En nøkkel ikke `null`, men kan en verdi.

trans-unit.source: The key is handled in a case-insensitive manner; it is translated to lowercase before it is used with the string dictionary.
trans-unit.target: Nøkkelen behandles i en samlingstype måte; Det oversettes til små bokstaver før den brukes med ordlisten streng.

trans-unit.source: In .NET Framework version 1.0, this class uses culture-sensitive string comparisons.
trans-unit.target: I .NET Framework, versjon 1.0 bruker denne klassen kultur sensitive strengsammenligninger.

trans-unit.source: However, in .NET Framework version 1.1 and later, this class uses <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture%2A?displayProperty=fullName> when comparing strings.
trans-unit.target: I .NET Framework, versjon 1.1 og nyere, bruker imidlertid denne klassen <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture%2A?displayProperty=fullName>ved sammenligning av strenger.</xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: For more information about how culture affects comparisons and sorting, see [Performing Culture-Insensitive String Operations](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
trans-unit.target: Du finner mer informasjon om hvordan kultur påvirker sammenligninger og sortering [utfører kultur bokstaver strengoperasjoner](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: Den `foreach` -setningen for språket C# (`for each` i Visual Basic) skjuler av hvor komplekse enumeratorene.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: Ved hjelp av derfor `foreach` anbefales, i stedet for direkte manipulering enumeratoren.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratorene kan brukes til å lese data i samlingen, men de kan ikke brukes til å endre den underliggende samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: I utgangspunktet er enumeratoren plassert før det første elementet i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>henter også enumeratoren tilbake til denne plasseringen.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: At this position, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: På denne plasseringen <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>er udefinert.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Du må derfor kalle <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>å flytte enumeratoren til det første elementet i samlingen før leser <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>Returnerer det samme objektet før enten <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>eller <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>angir <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>til neste element.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>formidler slutten av samlingen enumeratoren er plassert etter det siste elementet i samlingen og <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerer `false`.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: Når enumeratoren er på denne plasseringen, etterfølgende kall til <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>også returnere `false`.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: Hvis siste kall til <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerte `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>er udefinert.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Angi <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>til det første elementet i samlingen på nytt, kan du kalle <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>etterfulgt av <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: En opplisting forblir gyldig så lenge samlingen forblir uendret.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du endrer til samlingen, for eksempel å legge til, endre eller slette elementer, enumeratoren ugyldiggjøres, og virkemåten er ikke definert.

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratoren har ikke eksklusiv tilgang til samlingen. lister opp i en samling er derfor gjelder ikke en sikker-prosedyre.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: For å garantere tråd sikkerhetsnivået under opplisting, kan du låse samlingen under hele opplistingen.

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: Du må implementere din egen synkronisering for å tillate samlingen for å få tilgang til flere tråder for lesing og skriving.

trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>forekomsten er ikke synkronisert.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>

trans-unit.source: Derived classes can provide a synchronized version of the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> using the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary.SyncRoot%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Avledede klasser kan gi en synkroniserte versjon av den <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>ved hjelp av den <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary.SyncRoot%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary.SyncRoot%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>

trans-unit.source: Enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: Lister opp i en samling vil si gjelder ikke sikker.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: Selv når en samling synkroniseres, kan andre tråder fortsatt endre samlingen, som fører til at enumeratoren til Iverksett et unntak.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: For å garantere tråd sikkerhetsnivået under opplisting, kan du låse samlingen under hele opplistingen eller opp unntak som er et resultat av endringer foretatt av andre tråder.

trans-unit.source: Gets a collection of keys in the <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Henter en samling av nøkler i den <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The order of the keys in the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> is unspecified, but it is the same order as the associated values in the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> returned by the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary.Values%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Rekkefølgen på nøklene i den <xref:System.Collections.ICollection>er ikke angitt, men det er den samme rekkefølgen som de tilhørende verdiene i den <xref:System.Collections.ICollection>returnert av den <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary.Values%2A>metoden.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary.Values%2A> </xref:System.Collections.ICollection> </xref:System.Collections.ICollection>

trans-unit.source: The returned <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> is not a static copy; instead, the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> refers back to the keys in the original <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>.
trans-unit.target: Det returnerte <xref:System.Collections.ICollection>er ikke en statisk kopi; i stedet <xref:System.Collections.ICollection>refererer tilbake til nøklene i opprinnelige <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> </xref:System.Collections.ICollection> </xref:System.Collections.ICollection>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, changes to the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> continue to be reflected in the <xref:System.Collections.ICollection>.
trans-unit.target: Endrer derfor <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>fortsette skal vises i <xref:System.Collections.ICollection>.</xref:System.Collections.ICollection> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>

trans-unit.source: Retrieving the value of this property is an O(1) operation.
trans-unit.target: Henting av verdien for denne egenskapen er en O(1)-operasjon.

trans-unit.source: An <xref:System.Collections.ICollection> that provides the keys in the <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Collections.ICollection>som inneholder nøklene i den <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"> </xref>.</xref:System.Collections.ICollection>

trans-unit.source: Removes the entry with the specified key from the string dictionary.
trans-unit.target: Fjerner posten med den angitte nøkkelen fra ordlisten streng.

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> does not contain an element with the specified key, the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: Hvis den <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>ikke inneholder et element med den angitte nøkkelen i <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>forblir uendret.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>

trans-unit.source: No exception is thrown.
trans-unit.target: Ingen unntak.

trans-unit.source: The key is handled in a case-insensitive manner; it is translated to lowercase before it is used to find the entry to remove from the string dictionary.
trans-unit.target: Nøkkelen behandles i en samlingstype måte; Det oversettes til små bokstaver før den brukes til å finne oppføringen for å fjerne fra ordlisten streng.

trans-unit.source: This method is an O(1) operation.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden er en O(1)-operasjon.

trans-unit.source: The key of the entry to remove.
trans-unit.target: Nøkkelen for å fjerne.

trans-unit.source: The key is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: The key is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"></xref> is read-only.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"> </xref> er skrivebeskyttet.

trans-unit.source: Gets an object that can be used to synchronize access to the <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Henter et objekt som kan brukes til å synkronisere tilgang til den <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Derived classes can provide their own synchronized version of the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> using the SyncRoot property.
trans-unit.target: Avledede klasser kan gi sin egen synkroniserte versjon av den <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>ved hjelp av SyncRoot-egenskapen.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>

trans-unit.source: The synchronizing code must perform operations on the SyncRoot of the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>, not directly on the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>.
trans-unit.target: Synkronisering koden må utføre operasjoner på SyncRoot av den <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>, ikke direkte på <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>

trans-unit.source: This ensures proper operation of collections that are derived from other objects.
trans-unit.target: Dette sikrer ordentlig med samlinger som er avledet fra andre objekter.

trans-unit.source: Specifically, it maintains proper synchronization with other threads that might be simultaneously modifying the <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary> object.
trans-unit.target: Nærmere bestemt den opprettholder riktig synkronisering med andre tråder som kan være samtidig endring av <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>objektet.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary>

trans-unit.source: Enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: Lister opp i en samling vil si gjelder ikke sikker.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: Selv når en samling synkroniseres, kan andre tråder fortsatt endre samlingen, som fører til at enumeratoren til Iverksett et unntak.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: For å garantere tråd sikkerhetsnivået under opplisting, kan du låse samlingen under hele opplistingen eller opp unntak som er et resultat av endringer foretatt av andre tråder.

trans-unit.target: En <xref:System.Object>som kan brukes til å synkronisere tilgang til den <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringDictionary"> </xref>.</xref:System.Object>
